text.section:
The General Assembly finds and declares that, except for on premise advertising, outdoor advertising along and adjacent to the federal-aid primary system of highways is a commercial use of these highways that should be regulated to:
Prevent unreasonable distraction of the drivers of motor vehicles;
Prevent confusion as to traffic lights, signs, controls, or signals, and prevent interference with the effectiveness of traffic regulations;
Promote the prosperity, economic well-being, health, safety, morals, order, convenience, and general welfare of this State;
Promote the enjoyment of travel on and protection of the public investment in highways in this State; and
Preserve and enhance the natural scenic beauty or esthetic features and values of these highways and their adjacent areas.
